com.iha.emulator.utilities.watchers

Class ResponseTracker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iha.emulator.utilities.watchers.ResponseTracker

  • public class ResponseTracker
extends java.lang.Object
    Class responsible for storing server responses time. Also create statistical information about responses times as maximal responses per second or number of responses for current second.
    Author:
    Filip Sutovsky

      • ResponseTracker

        public ResponseTracker(boolean enabled)
        Creates response tracker and sets if it is enabled according to parameter. Responses are stored and statistical information gathering is disabled.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if response tracking is enabled, false otherwise

      • ResponseTracker

        public ResponseTracker(boolean enabled,
                       boolean dumpResponses)
        Creates response tracker, sets if it is enabled and if responses are stored according to parameters. Statistical information gathering is disabled.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if response tracking is enabled, false otherwise
        dumpResponses - true if responses shouldn't be stored, false otherwise

      • ResponseTracker

        public ResponseTracker(boolean enabled,
                       boolean dumpResponses,
                       boolean trackPerSecond)
        Creates response tracker, sets if it is enabled, if responses are stored and if statistical information are gathered according to parameters.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if response tracking is enabled, false otherwise
        dumpResponses - true if responses shouldn't be stored, false otherwise
        trackPerSecond - true if statistical information should be gathered, false otherwise

      • addResponse

        public void addResponse(long start,
                        long end)
        Adds new Response to responses list. If chart is assigned, adds response to chart as well. Also if statistical information gathering is enabled, measuring method is invoked Sets response value as start - end and time of response as end
        Parameters:
        start - response start time in milliseconds
        end - response end time in milliseconds
